According to the standard draft 10 that the README says this server conforms to, the Upgrade header should be handled case-insensitively. Currently it is handled case-sensitively.

middleware.py:

    def __call__(self, environ, start_response):
        # Initial handshake validation
        try:
            if 'websocket' not in environ.get('upgrade.protocol', ''):
                raise HandshakeError("Upgrade protocol is not websocket")

Hello @elapouya!

First of all, thank you for the marvelous work about docxtpl!! I would like to ask you if there is any simple way of create a numbered list in the template using this repo. For example, something like:

i=1
{%tr for text in infos %}
   {{ i }}. {{ text }}
   i = i+1
{%tr endfor %}

I tried this but without success. 

Thank you so much in advance. Regards!!

Hi!
When I try to use the formattingAdd setting, either in my settings.py file or in the model field, I get a whole lot of issues.
```
formattingAdd':{
    "red-p-add": {
        'title': 'Red Block Add',
        'args': ['p', 'class', 'red-styled']
    },
    "red-p-remove": {
        'title': 'Red Block Remove',
        'args': ['p', 'class', 'red-styled', 'remove']
    },
}
```
When applying globally, only one seemingly arbitrary style was added to the menu (Red Block Add) and was only wrapping text in <undefined> tags. When applying to the model, nothing appears at all in the menu and makemigrations doesn't detect any changes.

Thanks in advance.

Hi,

I have the following code and noticed a bug:

    subscription = recurly.Subscription(
			plan_code = 'pluskey',
			currency = 'EUR',
			quantity = request.form['plan_quantity'],
			account = account
    )
		
    subscription.preview()
    subscription.unit_amount_in_cents = 1200
    subscription.save()

`subscription.save()` then throws 

> ConnectionRefusedError: [WinError 10061] No connection could be made because the target machine actively refused it

I also think to know **why** this happens:

When calling `subscription.preview()` the attribute `subscription._url` gets set (to an empty string), and the `subscription.save()` method checks for it:

    if hasattr(self, '_url'):
        return self._update()
    return self._create()

But `.update()` can't be called because `_url` is empty thus resulting in an `ConnectionRefusedError`. I would suggest either modifying the `.preview()` method to not create the `_url` attribute or changing the `.save()` method to include an additional check like this:

    if hasattr(self, '_url'):
        if self._url:
            return self._update()
    return self._create()

**Observed:**

Pipenv lock file contains incompatible versions. Specifically I have fixed the version of six==1.10 under packages and left the version of behave free under dev-packages. Behave 1.2.6 is locked even though that version depends on six==1.11. The `pipenv install -d` also completes without errors installing the two incompatible versions.  (possibly related to #1220?)

Using pipenv version: 11.8.3

**Expected:**

Pipenv picks an older version of behave or at least issues an error if there is nothing it can do.


**Pipfile:**

    [[source]]
    url = "https://pypi.python.org/simple"
    name = "pypi"
    verify_ssl = true

    [packages]
    six = "==1.10.0"

    [dev-packages]
    behave = "*"

